result.execSummary:
The defendant Andrew M. Weissenborn was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Case called at 9:57am [mo]
Defendant Andrew M. Weissenborn in court with Attorney Nicole Nannette Schrier.   DA Susan Happ appears for the State of Wisconsin.
DA Happ verifies victim rights compliance

On State's Request to Amend Information:
--argument given by DA Happ
--the Court grants the State's request to amend the Information

Maximum penalties recited; Constitutional rights reviewed; plea of " NO CONTEST " entered on Count #1 of the Amended Information; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; the Court accepts the plea, finds Defendant guilty, and orders Judgment of Conviction entered.

On Motion of the State, the Court reads-in and dismisses Count #2.

Sentencing arguments given by Counsel

On Count #1, the Court withholds sentence, and places Defendant on Probation for 2 years.

The Court adopts the conditions as set forth in the CCS.

[which are:
--participate in on-going mental health treatment per agent
--to any undergo assessment, treatment, therapy and counseling as deemed appropriate by the Agent
--no possession of any dangerous weapon
--complete certified Batterers' Intervention programming or anger management one or the other or both at agent's discretion
--no acts or threats of violence
--to pay statutory costs, to include domestic abuse surcharge]

The Court adds the conditions:
--no contact with JMH during term of Probation
--not enter into any new intimate partner relationship without approval of agent


Days credit for time already served:  0  days

The Court determines that Mr. Weissenborn already has DNA sample on file, does not order another.
The Court modifies its previous order regarding repayment of attorney fees. Mr. Weissenborn is to now pay $50 per month towards attorney fees, on the same schedule as previously set.
The Court orders cash bond to be applied to costs/fees
